SUMMARY:Clown 200: Reinforcing Your Clown Foundation with Mick Holsbeke
DTSTAMP:20260306T013343Z
DTSTART:20260307T133000Z
DESCRIPTION:Deepen your clown craft through presence\\\, rhythm\\\, status\
	\\, and physical comedy—embracing failure to build confidence\\\, independ
	ence\\\, and play\\n\\n\\n\\nIn the Clown 200 class series\\\, students wi
	ll deepen their understanding of the foundations of theatrical clowning. P
	articipants will engage in exercises focused on presence\\\, rhythm\\\, te
	nsion\\\, emotional endurance\\\, character development\\\, status play\\\
	, and physical humor. By embracing failure and mistakes\\\, students build
	 confidence to take new comic risks\\\, grow in their comedic abilities\\\
	, and gently approach independence in harnessing the elusive state of Clow
	n. \\nClass Details\\nDates: 3/5/26 thru 4/9/26\; Six (6) Thursday classes
	 \\nTime: 1:30 – 3:00 PM \\nLocation: The Clown Garage at Improv School Ea
	stside Issaquah \\n1315 NW Mall Street\\\, Suite 4 Issaquah\\\, WA 98027 (
	next to the Gaslamp Bar & Grill) \\nMaximum students: 12 \\nAges: 18 plus 
	\\nCost: $320 \\nPrerequisite: None\n\nhttps://www.unexpectedproductions.o
	rg/event/clown-200-reinforcing-your-clown-foundation-with-mick-holsbeke/\n
